context: Many popular museums, such as the San Diego Museum of Art, the San Diego Natural History Museum, the San Diego Museum of Man, the Museum of Photographic Arts, and the <a4_0><b9_0>San Diego Air & Space Museum<b9_0/><a4_0/> are located in <a2_0><b7_0>Balboa Park<b7_0/><a2_0/>, which is also the location of the San Diego Zoo. <b5_0>The <a0_0>Museum of Contemporary Art San Diego (MCASD)<b5_0/><a0_0/> is located in La Jolla and has a branch located at the Santa Fe Depot downtown. The downtown branch consists of two building on two opposite streets. The <a1_0><b6_0>Columbia district downtown<b6_0/><a1_0/> is home to historic ship exhibits belonging to the San Diego Maritime Museum, headlined by the Star of India, as well as the unrelated <a3_0><b8_0>San Diego Aircraft Carrier Museum<b8_0/><a3_0/> featuring the USS Midway aircraft carrier.
